I've heard another version of that joke that, in my opinion, was way funnier (please read on ONLY after you watch the video to hear their joke first):


"Two hunters are out in the forest when one of them starts choking, collapses and goes unconscious.
The other hunter immediately calls 911: 'Please help! My friend just choked, collapsed and is unconscious'
'Calm down, we can help, can you tell us if he is breathing?'
'I don't know, I think so, but I'm not sure!'
'Well, we need to know for sure that he's not breathing'
There's a pause... then a shot is heard over the phone
'Ok, he is FOR SURE not breathing anymore, what do I do now?'"

My reasoning for why I think I find it funnier is because the friend is calling 911 for help. Even if he is incredibly stupid (which he would have to be for this joke) he is still ultimately trying to help his collapsed friend, so while it is implausible that someone who is trying to help their friend would shoot them to make sure they stop breathing if a 911 operator told them to do so, it is much less plausible that someone who is trying to help their friend would shoot them to make sure they are DEAD (thereby completely negating the whole "I'm trying to help my friend" thing) if a 911 operator told them to do so.

It's a very subtle change but I think it makes a huge difference.
